#eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 NEWCASTLE - Government has declared a State of Disaster to respond to flooding in seven provinces. The National Disaster Management Centre says they've received reports of flooded homes, vehicles swept away by floodwaters, overflowing dams and damage to infrastructure, roads and bridges. READ: KZN floods | Mother Nature wreaks havoc in Newcastle At least three people died in KwaZulu-Natal with dozens evacuated to community halls. This as heavy rain and floods have wreaked havoc in the province. READ: Newcastle flooding | Floods caused by heavy rains Cogta MEC Bongi Sithole visited affected areas in Newcastle. * eNCA's Siphamandla Goge reports.